And Edward, the one thing that struck me as I read your post--far more than the history and information you put up--was the fact that almost every statement you made, and every view you took of the situations involved, was intensely, vividly, and *blindly* American. <br>
<br>
Situations are evaluated and resolved as if the US is the only entity involved. I said in my previous post that many Americans feel very strongly that &quot;American ideals and way of life are superior to the rest of the world.&quot; I should also have said that sometimes the US forgets that the rest of the world is composed of human beings too.<br>
<br>
In terms of the Geneva Convention, Israel violates it on a daily basis. I invite anyone who disagrees to actually read the convention. Its at www.icrc.org. The violations will be readily apparent within a matter of minutes.<br>
<br>
For that matter, the recent US violations will also be apparent.<br>
<br>
=============================================<br>
<br>
Heres something to consider:<br>
<br>
Imagine if a country existed that devoted a huge amount of its GNP to building a vast sprawling military machine; a nation that had stockpiled chemical and nuclear weapons but continued to research technology that would further advance its already superior military edge; a country that had no problem whatsoever with interfering in the internal affairs of other countries, including funding guerillas and assasinating leaders it felt were undesirable; one that refused to sign international accords concerning warcrimes and torture that had been ratified by the rest of the world, because it didnt want to be held accountable to anyone other than itself; a country that repeatedly misled its population in wartime, to the point not only of controlling the press but outright lying about military activities and casualties and curtailing civil liberties under the guise of national security.<br>
<br>
Imagine that country...and then look at the US.<br>
<br>
If you dont believe me, I can provide countless examples to support my argument, many of them very recent past. <br>
<br>
